  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis power-law coefficients are drawn from the experimental regression reported in Giersiepen et al. (1990), as cited in the validation literature; the specific regression dataset is referenced via identifier https://doi.org/10.1016/0014-2999(90)90377-o.",
  "referencesIdentifier": "https://doi.org/10.1016/0014-2999(90)90377-o",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-mrl2",
